hopobject.body: Lost credit card retail price of trazodone There's risk in Snapchat, but more risk, say experts, in using your real name. Chris Watkins, a registered private investigator working with Stillinger Investigations, says that lying about your identity is key to not getting caught. "If I set up an e-mail account or social media account with false information, there would be no way to trace it back to me unless [someone] got in touch with the webmasters," he told ABC News.
